reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great luggage set!
reviews.reviewText: Beautiful luggage set! I got the black with brown detail. Lightweight, durable. Love the lock factor and the extendable options. The wheels are smooth rolling. Love that I Can pack everything in the largest suitcase for easy storage that doesn’t take up too much space. Great set and awesome value/deal.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice luggage not sure about the durability but hopeful
reviews.reviewText: I love the look of this suitcase, which is smaller than I was expecting, only because I didn't pay attention to the measurements. The good news is it is expandable and when paired with the toiletry and overnight bag made a good combination for a three day trip. It seems fairly rugged. I didn't fly but rather drove to my destination so not sure how it would hold up but you will not have to check it.The suitcase is expandable which helped a lot and maneuvered nicely through the hotel. It actually was fine size wise since I only took what I needed instead of over packing as usual, something I'm sure you never do! For the price I feel it was a good value for what I needed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worked well for 8 day vacay
reviews.reviewText: I got this set for a 8 day vacay to Mazatlan. So my clothing was not bulky. I was able to pack 4 bathing suits and like 4 pairs of shorts, 4 tank tops, 2 dresses, 1 romper, 2 pj's, 2 camisoles, undies, 3 pairs of socks, my water floaties, 2 tumblers, a brush, workout outfit, and a beach coverup and a kamoto. These clothes are lighter than winter wear and I was able to pack without opening the expansion. That was great and I love the look. The carrier bag was perfect for the pool it carried our 2 beach towels, sun glasses, 2 headphones, phones, sunscreen, 2 water bottles, tumblers. Was perfect. On the plain it carried all my liquids to travel carry-on. My airlines was Alaskan and I believe they are a little on the tight on the size. And it was fine. No one even checked. Lol. I did get a little rip in the pocket that you put over the luggage. But I did stuff it and was tightly wrapped on the luggage. I'm sure it wasn't ment to have so much pressure. I just hand-sewn a few stitches and it was back to normal. I do recommend it and it was very stylish. I feel it was the best looking luggage! Great to get as a gift too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Not bad for the price... however...
reviews.reviewText: The suitcase its self feels sturdy I loved it, however the expandable duffle bag zipper kept getting stuck and I was never able to close it properly. I ended up having to toss the duffle bag because it kept getting stuck with or without things inside. I liked how it expanded, it was disappointing that I could never get it to work properly. It is worth the price for a 3 pc however if I had known I would have had issues with the duffle bag I would've just purchased the suitcase for the same price somewhere else.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Looked a lot better than I expected and is great quality.I had promised myself I'd never check a hardside luggage again due to constant scratching but I ended up having to check this bag on a 24 hour trip and it held up with no issues at all!My softside luggage became very dirt on this trip.Long term durability to be determined, but this is a very nice product that's worth the money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Classy looking luggage
reviews.reviewText: I ordered the grey and let me tell you, it did not disappoint. Very classy looking. The tote bag is much larger than I expected. Love that every suitcase has side "legs" so when you lay it on its side, the bag itself doesn't lay on the ground. Great value for the money so far

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect Luggage for Family
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this set of luggage for myself but will be ordering the whole set for my family. Great compartments for organization, very sturdy, and aesthetically pleasing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful but poor stitching
reviews.reviewText: I’ve only used this set for about 6 domestic trips and the handbag is already ripping significantly. I typically put tea or Vitamin C pouches in the sleeve that wraps around the handle of the wheeled-bag so there isn’t much strain on it from what’s inside.I’ve received a lot of compliments on how classy this set looks and the wheeled carry on is very spacious and moves well on different types of surfaces.Unfortunately, after only 4 months of use, I might have to buy another hand bag which is a shame as they will no longer match at that point.Not a bad set for the price but be willing to spend more money a few months after you buy it to replace the handbag when it breaks.
